// Pseudo API Routes
// REST API endpoints for listing, reading, searching, and finding cross-references in .pseudo files across a project directory.
// synced: 2026-03-26T13:51:59Z

FUNCTION handlePseudoAPI(req: Request) -> Response [2026-03-26]                EXPORT
  Routes incoming requests to the appropriate handler based on path and method.
  Requires a `project` query param; returns 400 if absent.
  IF path is /files GET, CALL handleListFiles.
  IF path is /file GET, requires `file` param, CALL handleGetFile.
  IF path is /search GET, requires `q` param, CALL handleSearch.
  IF path is /references GET, requires `functionName` and `fileStem` params, CALL handleGetReferences.
  Any unmatched path returns 404. Errors return 500.

---

FUNCTION handleListFiles(project: string) -> Response [2026-03-26]
  Recursively walks the project directory and collects all .pseudo file paths.
  Step 1. walkDir: reads each directory entry; recurses into subdirectories.
  Step 2. For each .pseudo file, compute its path relative to project root and strip the .pseudo extension.
  Step 3. Sort the resulting stems alphabetically.
  Step 4. Return JSON { files: string[] }. Returns empty array on any error.

---

FUNCTION handleGetFile(project: string, file: string) -> Response [2026-03-26]
  Reads and returns the content of a single .pseudo file.
  Step 1. Append .pseudo extension if not already present; join with project root.
  Step 2. IF the exact path exists on disk, read and return { content, path }.
  Step 3. ELSE extract the basename from the file param and CALL findPseudoByBasename to search the tree.
  Step 4. IF found, read and return { content, path }. ELSE return 404.

---

FUNCTION findPseudoByBasename(dir: string, basename: string) -> string | null [2026-03-26]
  Recursively searches the directory tree for a .pseudo file whose filename is `<basename>.pseudo`.
  Returns the full path of the first match found, or null if none exists.
  Silently ignores unreadable directories.

---

FUNCTION handleSearch(project: string, query: string) -> Response [2026-03-26]
  Full-text search across all .pseudo files in the project, capped at 50 total matches.
  Step 1. Walk the directory tree; for each .pseudo file read its lines.
  Step 2. Track the current FUNCTION block by watching for lines starting with "function ".
  Step 3. For each line matching the query (case-insensitive), record line text, line number, whether it is a FUNCTION line, and the enclosing function name.
  Step 4. Within each file, sort matches so FUNCTION-line hits appear before body hits; then by line number.
  Step 5. Key results by the file's relative path (without .pseudo). Return JSON { matches }.
  Stop processing further files once 50 total matches are accumulated.

---

FUNCTION handleGetReferences(project: string, functionName: string, fileStem: string) -> Response [2026-03-26]
  Finds all functions in the project that declare a CALLS annotation pointing to the given function.
  Step 1. Build the search string: "CALLS: <functionName> (<fileStem>)".
  Step 2. Walk the directory tree; for each .pseudo file track the current FUNCTION block.
  Step 3. IF a line contains the search string and a current function is known, record { file, callerFunction }.
  Step 4. Deduplicate entries with the same file + callerFunction pair.
  Step 5. Return JSON { references }.

---

FUNCTION jsonError(message: string, status: number) -> Response [2026-03-26]
  Helper that returns a JSON response with { error: message } at the given HTTP status code.
